title: How fast is the Rasberry Pi 5 WiFi? #shorts #raspberrypi5 #wifi
description: Please note that I was not paid for this video. Raspberry Pi did send me a free Raspberry Pi 5 for me to test with.  #raspberrypi5 #raspberrypi4 #raspberrypi
transcript: This is a Raspberry Pi 5. Let's test how good theWi-Fi is on a Raspberry Pi 5. Got the Raspberry Pi 5 connected to OBS on this laptop I've also got an application called iPERF running on the Mac the Raspberry Pi's IP address is 192.168.085 it doesn't have an Ethernet cable connected it's connected via Wi-Fi to this router. Now this is obviously not a great test because the Raspberry Pi right next to the router but it gives us an indication of possible speeds. The Mac is also connected to the same Wi-Fi network. So on the Raspberry Pi I'll use the command iperf3 -s because it's the server and as you can see it's listening on Port 5201 on the Mac we'll connect to that IP address on Port 5201 and I'll click start. Here we're getting 120 megabits per second. So on the Mac you can see we're getting about 126 megabits per second I have had it go faster kind of depends but here's a very unscientific test of the Wi-Fi on a Raspberry Pi 5
